name: Mahapraja Bangli
address: Br Puraja, Peninjoan, Kec. Tembuku, Kabupaten Bangli, Bali 80671, Indonesia
review 1:
Good place for family activities.

The place is not too big but for me it's quite comfortable with the bed of green grass and playground for kids with long slides.

If you want to spend the night they have bamboo lodge for Rp. 450,000,- /night. But please be reminded that the lodge is not too suitable for older ones that have difficulties in walking.

They also have fruit-picking activites. They have tangerines, durian and guava trees that you can pick yourself.
review 2:
The first experience to visit this place is awesome, what I feel is a return to nature, beautiful, uncrowded and peaceful. Fresh air could certainly be felt because of the attractions located away from urban areas. There are several spot photos you can use to train your photography capabilities. Staff is very friendly and of course their native Balinese. In this place you can camp and rent small cottage to stay there.

NOTE :
If you want to visit this place, make sure you or the driver you are using has a pretty good driving skills because of the many road uphill and also the way that sharp cornering.
review 3: It is good to spend your weekend in Mahapraja. They have playground for kids, some photo spots, quite large camping ground (last time I brought group of 200 students). They also have 4 villas (3 build in bamboo).
review 4: Love the place! A great place to relax & recharge your self. If you're lucky (come on its season), they have durian also.. The best I've ever had!
review 5:
a perfect gateaway from city,its a peacefull retreat center in peninjoan village.
kinda hard to find cellular signal here but wifi on request will do the job just fine
